    capsule: "Chachi and Ohwun De Maal appear to be unremarkable Duros. Their blue skin, noseless faces, similar body types and slitted mouths contribute to their undifferentiated appearance, making them difficult to distinguish from each other. The De Maals own Docking Bay 94 and five other docking bays (27, 43, 67, 71, and 86), a service shuttle, and eight nearby warehouses charging 5 credits per ton per week, each holding 250 tons. Current relations with Jabba are strained after a Corellian smuggler defied quarantine and fled from their bay, costing them a season of business and their good name. They are devout Duros who follow in the traditions of their folks — walk quietly, talk quietly, play fairly. Their objective is to stay on Mos Eisley with their friends and make a decent, honest living.",
    source: "WEG40069 Galaxy Guide 7: Mos Eisley p.29-31"
