    equipment: "Video sensor, bipedal locomotion, olfactory sensor, microwave sensor, Arjan vocabulator, TranLang II Communication module, mid-body support",
    capsule: "JayNine-Five is a Roche J9 Worker Drone of indeterminable age, standing 1.9 meters tall with insectoid eyes and piston-like limbs. She would fall over if not for a mid-body support — the result of her co-workers unscrewing her hip joints after she tried to report their laziness; she spent three weeks rooted to the spot until a maintenance droid took pity on her. She follows regulations to the letter and is despised by most traders and smugglers. The spaceport control tower has three Human technicians (two on duty at a time) who are unconcerned about their job and routinely wave ships through regardless of database flags. J9-5 will often demand full investigations and keep ships in holding patterns, but is almost always overruled. The spaceport database is incredibly slow, and the central computer once tried to impound Moff Julstan's yacht. Landing permits cost 20-40 credits per day.",
