    capsule: "Drayk uses a GoCorp hoverscooter to get around — a speeder accident left him paralyzed from the waist down. The abbot of the Dim-U monastery is quite a jump from the political clerk of yesteryear. After the accident, he stopped chasing short-term goals and set out to build a personal fortune. The monastery runs a BoSS ship transponder forgery service. Drayk has an uncharacteristic soft spot for those he thinks are in trouble through events not of their own making, being what he calls 'a victim of circumstance' himself. A very calm man who plans as far ahead as possible with at least three contingencies for every problem, unruffled by most turns of events — the only time he gets excited is at the thought of an unhappy customer.",
