    specialAbilities: "",
    forcePoints: 0,
    characterPoints: 3,
    move: 10,
    equipment: "Merr-Sonn Model 44 blaster pistol (4D damage) in shoulder holster, comlink, macrobinoculars, datapad, hydrospanner, 3 medpacs, Rebel uniform, dark starglasses, Incom T-65B X-wing starfighter\nT-65B X-wing:\nCraft: Incom T-65B X-Wing Starfighter\nType: Space Superiority Fighter\nScale: Starfighter\nLength: 12.5 meters\nCrew: 1\nCargo: 110 kg\nConsumables: 1 week\nHyperdrive: x1\nNav Computer: Astromech (10 jumps)\nManeuverability: 3D\nSpace: 8\nAtmosphere: 365; 1,050 km/h\nHull: 4D\nShields: 1D\nSensors: Passive 25/0D, Scan 50/1D, Search 75/2D, Focus 3/4D\nWeapons:\n  4 Laser Cannons (fire-linked, front, FC: 3D, space: 1-3/12/25, atmo: 100-300/1.2/2.5km, damage: 6D)\n  2 Proton Torpedo Launchers (3 each, front, FC: 2D, space: 1/3/7, atmo: 30-100/300/700, damage: 9D)",
    capsule: "Mazer Rackus is a typical-looking Twi'lek with piercing green eyes and long cranial tentacles. Wears a standard flight suit instead of traditional Twi'lek robes. Stole his first starship from his father at age 16 and promptly crashed it onto a Rebel-held world. Captured, he convinced the Rebels of his 'loyalties' — though he admits he was more afraid of facing his father. Loud and brash, he hates to see anything beautiful damaged. Very sensitive about his piloting skills — nothing ever happens by accident. Adores speed and risks but steers clear of capital ships — not from fear of death, but fear of another crash and remembering his father.",
    source: "WEG40063 Galaxy Guide 9: Fragments from the Rim p.14"
