    equipment: "Comlink, datapad, mobile life support unit (provides continuous medical support, regulating movement and function of numerous damaged organs; Move: 5), 20,000 credits",
    capsule: "Once a brash, swaggering military officer with an inflated sense of personal honor, young Janq wound up on the losing end of a duel that nearly cost him his life. Internal injuries left him paralyzed from the waist down, forced to spend over a quarter of a century in a mobile life support pod. After bitter withdrawal, he slowly rebuilt his shattered life, developing a deep appreciation for all life and a hatred for those who kill without just cause. With like-minded patrons he founded House Paramexor, dedicated to eliminating those who deliberately kill for sport or profit. The guild only accepts murder contracts, keeps membership deliberately under 1,000, and provides hunters every possible service and luxury. It is said any member would willingly die for their guild master without hesitation.",
    source: "WEG40073 Galaxy Guide 10: Bounty Hunters p.98-99"
