    capsule: "Jalindas is the brains behind House Renliss. She originally served with her sister as part of an Imperial deep-cover security team, but suffered near-fatal injuries when their cover was blown and the principally male team members abandoned the sisters for dead. After months of evasion, they encountered a guild huntress who secured their passage to safety. The lack of proper medical attention cost Jalindas her right eye (replaced with a cybernetic implant) and required considerable facial reconstruction. She never forgave her team leader. Rather than return to Intelligence, the sisters adopted new identities and went underground for years, eventually surfacing at the head of a small but proficient group of female bounty hunters specializing in male-only contracts. Imperial Intelligence has since uncovered their identities but chose to utilize their skills rather than prosecute — select Intelligence directors use House Renliss for 'cleaning house.'",
    source: "WEG40073 Galaxy Guide 10: Bounty Hunters p.100-101"
