    equipment: "Comlink, blaster carbine (5D), hold-out blaster (3D), blast vest (+1D to front from physical, +1 energy)",
    capsule: "Llleag'Mak is a Kian'thar from Shaum Hii with a sophisticated version of his species' emotion-sensing ability — he can determine another being's emotional state and intent. He drifted into the criminal underworld naturally, quickly learning extortion, assault, and loan sharking. Rising through the ranks, he marked each promotion by the violent overthrow of a superior. When news of Jabba's death arrived, Llleag'Mak brought the words to his Hutt master — then immediately killed his superior and took his place. By playing up old hatreds and clan rivalries, he gained time to consolidate power. He never stays too long in one place, making him a difficult target. His real power lies in his connections with the spice trade — he currently controls several spice production and smuggling rings in the Inner Rim.",
